headline: Prologis (NYSE:PLD) Sees 7% Quarterly Dip Amid CEO Retirement News
summary: Prologis (NYSE:PLD) experienced a 7% price decline in the last quarter, a period marked by significant executive transitions and strong financial performance. The retirement announcement of CEO Hamid R. Moghadam along with the Board's bylaw updates signaled internal shifts, though likely had limited direct impact on investor sentiment.
